Dire Straits - Sultans Of Swing

* = C in bass, can be omitted

[Intro]
| [ch]Dm[/ch]     | [ch]Dm[/ch]  [ch]Dm/C[/ch]*|
| [ch]Dm[/ch]     | [ch]Dm[/ch]       |
| [ch]Dm[/ch]     | [ch]Dm[/ch]  [ch]Dm/C[/ch]*| x2

[Verse 1]
[tab]          [ch]Dm[/ch]                       [ch]C[/ch]              [ch]Bb[/ch]       [ch]A[/ch]
You get a shiver in the dark, it's raining in the park but meantime[/tab]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch]                        [ch]C[/ch]            [ch]Bb[/ch]         [ch]A[/ch]
  South of the river you stop and you hold everything[/tab]
[tab][ch]F[/ch]                                 [ch]C[/ch]
  A band is blowing Dixie double four time[/tab]
[tab][ch]Bb[/ch]                                            [ch]Dm[/ch]    [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
   You feel alright when you hear that music ring[/tab]

[Verse 2]
[tab]              [ch]Dm[/ch]                  [ch]C[/ch]         [ch]Bb[/ch]        [ch]A[/ch]
Well now, you step inside but you don't see too many faces[/tab]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch]                      [ch]C[/ch]                [ch]Bb[/ch]      [ch]A[/ch]
   Coming in out of the rain to hear the jazz go down[/tab]
[tab][ch]F[/ch]                       [ch]C[/ch]
  Competition in other places[/tab]
[tab][ch]Bb[/ch]                                     [ch]Dm[/ch]
   Uh, but the horns they blowin' that sound[/tab]
[tab][ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
        way on down south[/tab]
[tab][ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
        way on down south[/tab]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch]
London Town[/tab]

[Instrumental]
[ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
[ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]

[Verse 3]
[tab]             [ch]Dm[/ch]             [ch]C[/ch]  [ch]Bb[/ch]        [ch]A[/ch]
You check out Guitar George,     he knows all the chords[/tab]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch]                             [ch]C[/ch]               [ch]Bb[/ch]          [ch]A[/ch]
  Mind he's strictly rhythm he doesn't want to make it cry or sing[/tab]
[tab][ch]F[/ch]                           [ch]C[/ch]
  They say an old guitar is all he can afford[/tab]
[tab][ch]Bb[/ch]                                                 [ch]Dm[/ch]    [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
   When he gets up under the lights to play his thing[/tab]

[Verse 4]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch]                   [ch]C[/ch]    [ch]Bb[/ch]           [ch]A[/ch]
   And Harry doesn't mind if he doesn't make the scene[/tab]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch]                   [ch]C[/ch]         [ch]Bb[/ch]      [ch]A[/ch]
  He's got a daytime job, he's doin' alright[/tab]
[tab][ch]F[/ch]                                  [ch]C[/ch]
  He can play the honky tonk like anything[/tab]
[tab][ch]Bb[/ch]                               [ch]Dm[/ch]    [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
   Saving it up for Friday night[/tab]
[tab]                  [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
with the Sultans[/tab]
[tab]                    [ch]Dm[/ch]
with the Sultans of Swing[/tab]

[Instrumental]
[ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
[ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]

[Verse 5]
[tab]       [ch]Dm[/ch]                           [ch]C[/ch]        [ch]Bb[/ch]           [ch]A[/ch]
Then a crowd of young boys, they're foolin' around in the corner[/tab]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch]                                [ch]C[/ch]              [ch]Bb[/ch]            [ch]A[/ch]
   Drunk and dressed in their best brown baggies and their platform soles[/tab]
[tab][ch]F[/ch]                                        [ch]C[/ch]
  They don't give a damn about about any trumpet playin' band[/tab]
[tab][ch]Bb[/ch]                                   [ch]Dm[/ch]     [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
   It ain't what they call rock and roll[/tab]
[tab]                [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
and the Sultans[/tab]
[tab]                             [ch]Dm[/ch]
Yeah, the Sultans, they play Creole[/tab]

[Instrumental]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
...             Creole[/tab]
[ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]

[Lead]
| [ch]Dm[/ch]     | [ch]C[/ch]  [ch]Bb[/ch]  | [ch]A[/ch]      | [ch]A[/ch]       |

| [ch]F[/ch]      | [ch]F[/ch]      | [ch]C[/ch]      | [ch]C[/ch]       |
| [ch]Bb[/ch]     | [ch]Bb[/ch]     | [ch]Dm[/ch]     | [ch]Dm[/ch]  [ch]Bb[/ch]  |
| [ch]C[/ch]      | [ch]C[/ch]  [ch]Bb[/ch]  | [ch]C[/ch]      | [ch]C[/ch]       |

[Instrumental]
[ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
[ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]

[Verse 6]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch]                       [ch]C[/ch]         [ch]Bb[/ch]         [ch]A[/ch]
   And then the man he steps right up to the microphone[/tab]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch]              [ch]C[/ch]               [ch]Bb[/ch]        [ch]A[/ch]    ([ch]A7[/ch])
   And says at last just as the time bell ring[/tab]
[tab][ch]F[/ch]                      [ch]C[/ch]
  Goodnight, now it's time to go home[/tab]
[tab][ch]Bb[/ch]                                       [ch]Dm[/ch]     [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
   Then he makes it fast with one more thing[/tab]
[tab]                   [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
We are the Sultans[/tab]
[tab]                      [ch]Dm[/ch]
We are the Sultans of Swing[/tab]

[Instrumental]
[ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
[ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]

[Outro Solo]
[tab][ch]Dm[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch] - [ch]Bb[/ch] - [ch]C[/ch]
(repeat and fade, approx x7)[/tab]

recommended_tabs.version_description: This is an easy to follow and autoscroll friendly version. The "Em7 Bb9" measure at the end of each verse and also intro and solo parts is just two quick dtrums, one of each chord.
